@willholley
>Typically, CouchDB uses the [Review-Then-Commit](http://www.apache.org/foundation/glossary.html#ReviewThenCommit) (RTC) model of code collaboration, not _Commit-Then-Review_.

:stuck_out_tongue_winking_eye:

That's great @Sdas0000. Yeah, compaction level has to higher or equal than your log level, otherwise you won't see those messages. So for instance if you set your log level to `warning`, then your smoosh and couchdb `compaction_log_level` should be `warning`, `error`, etc to be logged.

Initially your log level was set to `error` but your `compaction_log_level` was at `notice` so you didn't see them. Then, when log level is `info`, you started seeing `notice` messages. `notice` is a big higher than `info` as per:

```erlang
level_to_integer(debug) -> 1;
level_to_integer(info) -> 2;
level_to_integer(notice) -> 3;
level_to_integer(warning) -> 4;
level_to_integer(warn) -> 4;
level_to_integer(error) -> 5;
level_to_integer(err) -> 5;
level_to_integer(critical) -> 6;
level_to_integer(crit) -> 6;
level_to_integer(alert) -> 7;
level_to_integer(emergency) -> 8;
level_to_integer(emerg) -> 8;
```

